<section xml:id="sec-arithmetic-with-complex-numbers">
    <title>Arithmetic with Complex Numbers</title>
    <introduction>
        <p>
            If you know how to add like terms and use the FOIL method, then addition, subtraction, and multiplication of complex numbers will seem very familiar.
            We will not cover division of complex numbers in this course.
        </p>
    </introduction>

    <subsection xml:id="subsec-adding-complex-numbers">
        <title>Adding Complex Numbers</title>

        <lemma xml:id="lem-how-to-add-complex-numbers">
            <title>How to Add Complex Numbers</title>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Let <m>a+bi</m> and <m>c+di</m> be any two complex numbers.
                    Then
                    <me>(a+bi)+(c+di)=(a+c)+(b+d)i</me>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    In other words, just add like terms.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </lemma>

        <example xml:id="ex-adding-two-complex-numbers">
            <title>Adding Two Complex Numbers</title>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Perform the operation <m>(3-4i)+(-2+9i)</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    <m>1+5i</m>
                </p>
            </answer>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>(3-4i)+(-2+9i)\amp=3-4i-2+9i</mrow>
                        <mrow>\amp=(3-2)+(-4i+9i)</mrow>
                        <mrow>\amp=1+5i</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
        <note xml:id="note-grouping-terms-and-negatives">
    <title>Grouping Terms and Negatives</title>
    <p>
        When grouping terms in parentheses, include any negative signs inside the parentheses and place a plus sign between the groups. This helps you avoid sign errors.
    </p>
</note>

    </subsection>

    <subsection xml:id="subsec-subtracting-complex-numbers">
        <title>Subtracting Complex Numbers</title>

        <lemma xml:id="lem-how-to-subtract-complex-numbers">
            <title>How to Subtract Complex Numbers</title>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Let <m>a+bi</m> and <m>c+di</m> be any two complex numbers.
                    Then
                    <me>(a+bi)-(c+di)=(a-c)+(b-d)i</me>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    In other words, distribute the negative and add like terms.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </lemma>

        <example xml:id="ex-subtracting-two-complex-numbers">
            <title>Subtracting Two Complex Numbers</title>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Perform the operation <m>(-3+2i)-(-5+3i)</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    <m>2-i</m>
                </p>
            </answer>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>(-3+2i)-(-5+3i)\amp=-3+2i+5-3i</mrow>
                        <mrow>\amp=(-3+5)+(2i-3i)</mrow>
                        <mrow>\amp=2-i</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
    </subsection>

    <subsection xml:id="subsec-multiplying-complex-numbers">
        <title>Multiplying Complex Numbers</title>

        <lemma xml:id="lem-how-to-multiply-complex-numbers">
            <title>How to Multiply Complex Numbers</title>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Let <m>a+bi</m> and <m>c+di</m> be any two complex numbers.
                    Then
                    <me>(a+bi)(c+di)=(ac-bd)+(ad+bc)i</me>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    In other words, just FOIL it out and simplify using <m>i^2=-1</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </lemma>

        <example xml:id="ex-multiply-two-complex-numbers">
            <title>Multiply Two Complex Numbers</title>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Perform the operation <m>(-6+5i)(2-i)</m>.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    <m>-7+16i</m>
                </p>
            </answer>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <md>
                        <mrow>(-6+5i)(2-i)\amp=-12+6i+10i-5i^2</mrow>
                        <mrow>\amp=-12+16i-5(-1)</mrow>
                        <mrow>\amp=-7+16i</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
    </subsection>
</section>
